{
  "texts": [
    "For the last three cases, the traditional K-fold cross-validation strategy (2-Fold, 3-Fold, and 5-Fold) was implemented, where K-1 subsets were used for training, and the remaining subset was used for testing.",
    "Furthermore, the K-Folds in the third and fourth cases were repeated two times to obtain more representative results.",
    "The obtained results are summarized in Figures 6 and 7, where the height of the bars represents the average metric values across folds.",
    "The vertical lines within each bar indicate the average minus and plus one standard deviation (SD) values of Cor obtained across folds.",
    "In the first of these figures (Figure 6), a deterioration in the normalized root mean squared error is observed as the training size decreases (moving right to left on the Percentage_tr axis) in both explored models."
  ]
}